Diskuze č.553635, vloženo 15.08.2011 02: _[_S_t_a_r_š_í_ _z_p_o_v_ě_ď_]_[_N_o_v_ě_j_š_í_ _z_p_o_v_ě_ď_]_[_H_l_a_v_n_í
41:49                                    _s_t_r_á_n_k_a_]
Homosexuálové vs. pedofilové
The vastly different treatment of homosexuals and paedophiles (elite of the
society vs worst criminals) shows how totally irrational the attitude of the
modern society to the topics of sexual orientation has become. One may be born
with homosexual or pedophilic inclinations - or any other inclination that
differs from the majority. So biologically, there's no difference between these
two conditions.

Also, the consensuality isn't the issue here because paedophiles are being
prosecuted even for non-physical things - like storing child pornography on
their PCs - that don't affect any children and that would surely be tolerable
(in a mandatory way) for gays etc. Moreover, many children could actually
happily collaborate with the paedophiles and they would enjoy "it", whatever
"it" is - and this has actually happened many times in the past, too. So even
in this respect, the situations are analogous.

So I agree that if one says that "homophobia" (and the idea that gays are a
promiscuit group that spreads HIV at the 200 times higher rate) is irrational,
we must say that the fear "what would paedophiles do to my or other children"
is also irrational. Both of them are justified by some excessive correlations;
both of them may be considered stereotypes that hurt a minority, too. I know
that these statements by two of us sound provocative but they're only
provocative because the whole homosexualism movement is based on totally
indefensible foundations and double standards in the treatment of various
conditions and the advocates of homosexualism are scared of the idea that
someone like us reminds them of these foundations.


The "quantitative correlations" do inevitably play a role when a rational
person is deciding whether a deviation XY from the average is tolerable.
Allowing some arguments ("it's not his fault") in one case but not in another
case is just wrong.

Tohle je názor jednoho českého bloggera píšícího anglicky. Good point, abych
tak řekl. Přesně to vystihuje i můj názor - proč se s homosexuály jedná jinak,
než s pedofily, když se tyto úchylky v zásadě neliší?
